The article is a readout of a meeting between President Obama and the Dalai Lama. The Dalai Lama offered his condolences for the shooting in Orlando and the President commended his efforts to promote compassion and respect. They discussed the situation for Tibetans in China, with the President expressing support for their rights and preservation of their traditions. The President encouraged dialogue between the Dalai Lama and Chinese authorities to lower tensions. He reiterated the US position that Tibet is part of China and does not support Tibetan independence. The Dalai Lama stated that he is not seeking independence and hopes for dialogue to resume. They also discussed the importance of a constructive relationship between the US and China. The President praised the Dalai Lama's leadership on climate change and his efforts to raise awareness.